      "side": 1,
      "message": "Thank you for the feedback, @geissonator@yahoo.com.\n\n@hariharanr@ami.com \u0027s confirmation matches my experience exactly — this error\noccurs consistently on a fresh Ubuntu 24.04 install when building\nOpenBMC natively (outside Docker/CI). The CI build systems likely\ndon\u0027t hit this because they run inside Docker containers where the\nAppArmor restriction doesn\u0027t apply.\nThe restriction was introduced in Ubuntu 24.04 via:\n  kernel.apparmor_restrict_unprivileged_userns \u003d 1\nThis is enabled by default in Ubuntu 24.04 but not in earlier LTS\nreleases, which explains why it wasn\u0027t reproducible on existing\nbuild systems. Developers setting up a fresh Ubuntu 24.04 host will\nreliably hit this without the fix.\nReference: https://gerrit.openbmc.org/c/openbmc/openbmc/+/78891",
